article.headline: Grant-Foster's 16 lead Grand Canyon over Utah Tech 73-61

images.name: Gabe McGlothan throws down powerful dunk vs. Utah Tech Trailblazers
images.caption: Gabe McGlothan throws down powerful dunk vs. Utah Tech Trailblazers

article.linkText: Grant-Foster's 16 lead Grand Canyon over Utah Tech 73-61
article.story: PHOENIX -- — Tyon Grant-Foster's 16 points helped Grand Canyon defeat Utah Tech 73-61 on Thursday. Grant-Foster added five rebounds and four steals for the Antelopes (23-2, 13-1 Western Athletic Conference). Gabe McGlothan added 12 points while going 4 of 11 (3 for 5 from 3-point range), and he also had eight rebounds and three steals. Rayshon Harrison shot 5 for 12, including 1 for 4 from beyond the arc to finish with 12 points. It was the sixth straight victory for the Antelopes. The Trailblazers (10-15, 6-8) were led by Tanner Christensen, who posted 18 points, 10 rebounds and five assists. Unisa Turay added 14 points for Utah Tech. Noa Gonsalves also had 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
